blog.name: cupcakegumbo
blog.title: Cupcake Gumbo Impoverished Artist
blog.description:
Hi, I'm Kat. 
I'm an artist with anxiety disorder and clinical depression. I'm trying to improve both my art and my mental state by blogging, (here) and doing art videos (on YouTube). 
I don't think I'm a very good artist, but I love art of just about any kind; and I'm actively trying to improve my artwork.
I consider myself to be "Impoverished" due to my mental health disorders. It's very difficult for me to find a job, and or keep one for any length of time due to my anxiety.
For some reason, no one really want's to take a chance on someone who stutters, cry's, and shakes under high stress... go figure.

title: Still Shaken.
body:
Yesterday messed me up more than I thought it did. I find myself still very fragile, and even the smallest thing sets me to trembling. I spent most of the day playing a video game; trying to hide most likely. At one point my hubby came in and sat next to me. My brain on auto pilot, I asked how he was doing. I didn’t even register that he had answered me as I just kept playing the game. He waited for a few moments and then left the bedroom. After a while, he came back in and waited till I was at a pause point. I thought he wanted to play the game so I offered to swap out with him. He said “Maybe, but first I want to talk to you.”

I knew at that moment that I had done something wrong, and asked him what had happened. He talked about how he had come in and I had asked him how he was doing, he said that he told me, “not very well actually”, and then he waited. I didn’t even look at him, I just kept playing the game in silence. So he got up and left the room, wondering if I was purposely ignoring him when he really needed my attention. Then he began wondering if he had done something wrong, and I was punishing him for it by ignoring him.

The fact that he actually worked up the energy to talk to me and ask if he had done something wrong, showed that he was really hurting about the silent treatment I had given him. Even though it was completely unintentional, I had hurt him deeply. I did my best to reassure him, and then I completely fell apart. I could not let go of the fact that I had not even noticed that he was doing bad and that I hurt him. The fact that I had done that to him, completely shattered me and sent me into a panic attack. I realize that I am so emotionally burnt out, that I don’t even have the capacity to help, or even register that my hubby needed help.

My nerves are so raw, but I don’t know what to do about it. He doesn’t do well with silence, because the little voice in his head begins telling him just how bad and unworthy he is. It doesn’t matter that none of it is true, a lifetime of emotional and verbal abuse has left him just as fragile as I am. I feel so lost right now, and have no idea what to do.
